Samalinh spewed out a flame. This tall Slak person ignited a small patch of forest and then circled above it, observing the timing. Interestingly, when he slowed down, the strange screams behind him also stopped. Samalinh forgot that there was a passenger on his back.
"Please, Tenuk, you've transformed into a Slak before, haven't you!"
"Flying yourself and being suddenly dragged away by a giant pink dragon are two different things!"
"Are you okay, Kayel?"
Kayel clearly disagreed with Nish's statement. He looked paler than usual, and his claws had deeply buried themselves in Samalinh's back, drawing blood. However, Samalinh seemed not to care. Nonetheless, Samalinh realized he had frightened his new friend and thus landed on an open ground.
"Sorry sorry, I caught a whiff of something. I need to deal with it!"
"Do you have to drag us along too?" Tenuk climbed off Sarslin, slid down along the tail, and asked with a sharp tone. "We left Revtvik behind! We abandoned that big, brawny guy! How is he supposed to find us?"
"He'll figure it out... " Nix sighed. "Revtvik might be slow, but he's not dumb."
"Does Revtvik know how to drive?"
Nix blinked, turned her head, and looked at Tenuk. "Of course he knows how to drive."
“Have you ever seen Latvik drive a car? He doesn't have a truck like yours, and I've never seen him drive a cute little car like Kayler's. He started riding the bus to work only because you always drove us to work.”
A laugh interrupted them. Sarslin suddenly burst into uncontrollable laughter, but no one knew why. It took Sarslin a long time to calm down.
"Sorry, sorry. I just imagined your big armored friend riding a mini bike designed for Themos children. That image was too funny! I wish I had telepathy. This idea is too good. I must treasure it!"
Kayler also laughed as he could imagine what Sarslin was thinking. "Alright, alright. But what did you smell? Why did you fly so fast?"
Sarslin grunted and took off, disappearing quickly before returning and leaving a corpse in front of Nix. It was an Orozarak, a very rare golden-white dragon-like creature. But its head was gone. "Another one has died. I heard their cries and smelled their blood. I must protect them and hunt the killer. This is Isini's will. Those creatures are nearby."
The powerful Slacker suddenly stiffened. Nix and Cayle also stiffened, their attention drawn to a gap at the edge of the open space. A huge, black creature was staring at them, hissing. This thing suddenly spread its two pairs of enormous wings and rushed forward, its target directly aimed at Sasa林, completely ignoring the three small figures in its way. Cayle and Tenuk barely managed to dodge to the side, but Nix found herself dragged to the ground, almost being thrown onto Sasa林.
Sasa林 grabbed Nix with its long, agile tail and tossed her onto its back, then took off into the air. The black creature with two pairs of wings quickly caught up.
Cayle made a clicking sound, drew a rifle from behind, and opened a bag, taking out a magazine of bullets. He hung the magazine around his chest for easy access, but soon realized that Nix, Sasa林, and the monster had disappeared without a trace.
"Hey, Tenuk, can you transform into a flying animal?" Cayle asked.
"Do you want to catch up?"
"Nonsense."
"But... one of them is a giant monster!"
"So what? This rifle in my hand has strong firepower and can shoot at any time. I just need to see it to bring it down."
Tennuk hesitated for a moment, then took a step back to give himself some space. With a low, painful moan, Tennuk's body stretched out, his fur turning into scales, and his arms transforming into wings. He quickly became a普通的浅蓝色斯拉克人，但眼睛仍然是红色的.
"Come up."
#1 <s>Tenuck now looked like an ordinary Slark, with neatly arranged scales on his back and a pair of spines that made it easier for Kayel to grab him. It took Tenuck a long time to take off, but once he ascended, he quickly adjusted his direction and tried to catch up.
#2 <s>However, Tenuck and Kayel soon realized they were not dealing with just one opponent. A second dark monster darted out from beneath them, and Tenuck barely dodged the impact.
#3 <s>"I guess this is the other terrifying big monster Ranelix was worried about?" Kayel frowned, trying to shoot at the second monster but missing, and quickly reloaded.
#4 <s>Tenuck did not respond; he was busy flying toward Nishi and Sazalin, even as the other monster was chasing them. Kayel awkwardly turned around to face the monster. He thought this was good news because he could aim and shoot more easily. Two bullets pierced the monster's upper wing, and it let out a painful roar before disappearing into the woods. Kayel was unsure if it was still following them, but he felt confident it would not be able to keep up.
#5 <s>Ahead, Sazalin was wildly thrashing, spraying flames at the black monster, while Nishi desperately clung to him to avoid falling. Although the monster was certainly injured, it seemed to be angered and unwilling to retreat, and the fireballs didn't seem to cause much harm. After steadying himself, Sazalin took the opportunity to draw his weapon, which was a trusted shotgun. Of course, a shotgun couldn't do much against such a monster, but the scattered bullets might at least scare off this black beast?
